1.Question : Write program demonstrates how to use regular expressions in Python to match and search for
patterns in text.


Code : 
import re

text = "NLP is amazing. NLP helps machines understand language."
match = re.search(r"NLP", text)

if match:
    print("First Match Found:", match.group())
all_matches = re.findall(r"NLP", text)
print("All Matches:", all_matches)


Output : 
First Match Found: NLP
All Matches: ['NLP', 'NLP']
